The instruction is to standardize the capitalization so that column C mirrors the case style of column B while keeping the correct tense. Therefore, for each data row we will:
1. Read the value in column B.
2. Read the value in column C (the tense‑converted word).
3. If column B is all lower‑case (`str.islower()`), force column C to lower‑case.
4. Otherwise (title‑case or mixed), convert column C to title‑case (`str.title()`), which matches the typical “proper” case shown in the sample.

We will write the adjusted value back into column C for every row that contains data. After saving, we will call `recalculate` to ensure any formulas are evaluated, then verify a few rows.
